{{Infobox zoo |zoo_name = Aquatopia |logo = |logo_caption = |image = Aquatopia - Annemoonvisjes.jpg |image_caption = Clownfishes in Aquatopia |location = [[Antwerp]], [[Belgium]] |date_opened = |date_closed = |coordinates = {{Coord|51|13|9|N|4|25|16|E|region:BE_type:landmark|display=it}} |area = |num_species = |num_animals = |largest_tank_vol = |total_tank_vol = {{Convert|1000000|l}} |annual_visitors = |members = |exhibits = |website = [http://www.aquatopia.be www.aquatopia.be] }}
'''Aquatopia''' was a popular educational attraction in central [[Antwerp]], [[Belgium]]. It used to feature a set of aquariums, along with recreations of other marine habitats, including swamps, rain forests, river deltas, and coral reefs. Aquatopia also included a number of special exhibits covering sharks, nautilus, and mysteries of the deep. The multi-story attraction was located on Koningin Astridplein, opposite [[Antwerpen-Centraal railway station]]. It had {{Convert|1000000|l}} of water.
Although the entrance to [[Antwerp Zoo]] is also located very close by, facing the same square (Astridplein), the zoo was not affiliated with Aquatopia.
Aquatopia closed on January 8, 2017.<ref>http://www.aquatopia.be/en/news/closing-8th-january</ref>
