[[File:Three Greek beers.jpg|thumb|Three tins of Greek beers]]
In [[Ancient Greece]], [[beer]] wasn't produced domestically, although it was widely consumed.   The first breweries in Greece were founded around the end of the 19th century.  The most widely known brands in Greece are: 

* [[Mythos (beer)|Mythos]]
* [[Athenian Brewery]]
* [[Fix (beer)|Fix]]
* [[Macedonian Thrace Brewery]]
* [[Peiraiki]]<ref>http://www.zingarate.com/network/atene/3-birre-greche-che-dovreste-conoscere.html Greek Beers</ref>
*[[Santorini Brewing Company]]

