'''Dalloz''' is a [[France|French]] publisher that specializes in legal matters and is France's main legal publisher.  It was founded by [[D√©sir√© Dalloz]] and his brother [[Armand Dalloz|Armand]] in 1845.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=kfdBAAAAYAAJ&printsec=frontcover&dq=Jurisprudence+g%C3%A9n%C3%A9rale+du+Royaume+en+mati%C3%A8re+civile,+commerciale+1824&hl=fr&sa=X&ei=R9UeUfa1I47KsgbS-oDACw&ved=0CDIQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=Jurisprudence%20g%C3%A9n%C3%A9rale%20du%20Royaume%20en%20mati%C3%A8re%20civile%2C%20commerciale%201824&f=false Premier volume], Paris, Imprimerie J. Smith, 1824 [en ligne]</ref> 

Among other collections (Precis dalloz...), Dalloz is known for its encyclopedia of law that covers different branches of law : civil law, business law, international law, criminal law, European law, etc.  Dalloz has published commentary, cases and legislation in a series of bulletins referred to generally as '''''Recueil Dalloz'''''. <ref>[http://www.periodicals.com/stock_f/r/ttl05929.html  Reprint from Schmidt Periodicals GmbH]</ref>

* ''Recueil Dalloz'' (1945‚Äì1964);
* ''Recueil Dalloz Sirey de doctrine, de jurisprudence et de l√©gislation'' (1965‚Äì1996);
* ''Recueil Dalloz''  (1997‚Äì1999);
* ''Recueil le Dalloz'' (1999- )  Published weekly.

Some topics are now only available online.

