The '''Military Committee for National Recovery''' ([[Arabic language|Arabic]]: ÿßŸÑŸÖÿ¨ŸÑÿ≥ ÿßŸÑÿπÿ≥ŸÉÿ±Ÿä ŸÑŸÑÿ•ŸÜÿπÿßÿ¥ ÿßŸÑŸàÿ∑ŸÜŸä) was a short-lived military government of the [[Islamic Republic of Mauritania]] after the [[coup d'√©tat]] that removed long-time [[President of Mauritania|President]] [[Mukthar Ould Daddah]] on July 10, 1978, until a second coup on April 6, 1979. It was headed by [[Col.]] [[Mustapha Ould Salek]]. It was followed by a second [[Military dictatorship|junta]], the [[Military Committee for National Salvation]] (CSMN).

