'''''The Yacoubian Building''''' ({{lang-ar|ÿπŸÖÿßÿ±ÿ© ŸäÿπŸÇŸàÿ®ŸäÿßŸÜ}} '' øImƒÅrat Ya øq≈´bƒ´ƒÅn'')  is a 2007 [[Egyptian television series]] based on the scenario of Atef Beshai and directed by Ahmad Saqr. The series featured major roles by [[Salah Al-Saadni]], [[Ezzat Abu Ouf]], [[Lobna Abdel Aziz]], Rania Youssef and [[Aser Yasin]].

The television series is based on the 2002 [[novel]] ''[[The Yacoubian Building]]'' by Egyptian author [[Alaa Al Aswany|Alaa el-Aswany]] and the 2006 film ''[[The Yacoubian Building (film)|The Yacoubian Building]]'' by [[Marwan Hamed]], with the mentioning of the character of the [[homosexuality|homosexual]] in the film original being excised from the TV series adaptation of the novel because of its controversial nature in the Arabic culture.

